Patch Set 1:

So, if I understand correctly, this is done automagically by running "tox -egenconfig && mv etc/glance-api.conf.sample etc/glance-api.conf", right?

Shouldn't we do that every time there is a change in the options? Couldn't we enforce that it is done by using a git hook?

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Since that conflict is -2ed and I agree with Erno there, I suggest we go along with this. Do we have any recommended times when we do this? Or do we just do this when convenient.

Also do we need to document that some of the default values are changing?

Patch Set 3:

> Since that conflict is -2ed and I agree with Erno there, I suggest
 > we go along with this. Do we have any recommended times when we do
 > this? Or do we just do this when convenient.
 > 
 > Also do we need to document that some of the default values are
 > changing?

Thanks Niall. This patch was done to help push the release notes out https://review.openstack.org/#/c/323652/ as the bug fixes have been included in n-1. However, the config are being generated in the doc pages now, so I didn't have to add dependency of this patch on the release notes. 

In a gist, this is a one off patch that is supposed to address the bugs.

The general regeneration/refresh of the configs is done just prior to milestone-3 each cycle.

Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1 Workflow+1

This has been sitting in the queue without any +/- reviews for a long time. We need to fix these related bugs as the configs are going to ship in tree.

We have about a week time before the final non-client libs can be released. In such a situation, it's vital that these configs are sync in glance tree so that if a bug appears/regression appears after the sync we can take appropriate action.
